lead_paragraph: A timely idea is that of Mrs. Anthony J. Drexel Biddle, wife of our Ambassador to the Governments in Exile, to send a group of ten representative American women to England, there to see at first-hand the conditions under which their sisters are living and working to bring this war to a successful conclusion.
